    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>All examples use discrete finite distributions. The data processing inequality holds for continuous distributions, Markov kernels, and general measurable spaces. The inequality is tight (equality) when Y is a sufficient statistic for X with respect to Z. Every example computes entropy directly from probability vectors rather than simulating the Markov chain.</p>


